text.section:
A Class 6 pub-brewery license shall be issued:
By the State Comptroller;
Only to a holder of a Class B beer, wine and liquor (on-sale) license that is issued for use on the premises of a restaurant located in the jurisdictions permitted by this subsection;
In the City of Annapolis; and
Throughout the State, but not in the following subdivisions:
Allegany County;
Caroline County;
Howard County;
St. Mary's County; and
Somerset County.

section.section:
This subsection applies only in the following jurisdictions:
City of Annapolis;
Anne Arundel County;
Baltimore City;
Baltimore County;
Calvert County;
Cecil County;
Charles County;
Harford County;
Prince George's County;
Talbot County;
Wicomico County; and
Worcester County.
